  "body": "**Description**\r\nHow to simulate transaction and trace it?\r\nMy code can trace the transaction, but next transaction of same sender are fails with 'bad nonce' error.\r\n```csharp\r\npublic class TestTransactionTracer : ITxTracer\r\n{\r\n...\r\n    public bool IsTracingState { get; } = true;\r\n    public bool IsTracingReceipt { get; } = true;\r\n    public bool IsTracingActions { get; } = true;\r\n    public bool IsTracingOpLevelStorage { get; } = true;\r\n    public bool IsTracingMemory { get; } = true;\r\n    public bool IsTracingInstructions { get; } = true;\r\n    public bool IsTracingRefunds { get; } = true;\r\n    public bool IsTracingCode { get; } = true;\r\n    public bool IsTracingStack { get; } = true;\r\n    public bool IsTracingBlockHash { get; } = true;\r\n    public bool IsTracingAccess { get; } = true;\r\n    public bool IsTracingFees { get; } = true;\r\n    public bool IsTracing { get; } = true;\r\n    public bool IsTracingStorage { get; } = true;\r\n...\r\n}\r\n```\r\n```csharp\r\nvar tracer = new TestTransactionTracer(); // my test tracer\r\nusing (var processor = new ReadOnlyTransactionProcessor(_api.TransactionProcessor, _api.WorldState, _api.WorldState.StateRoot)) {\r\n    //processor.CallAndRestore(transaction, header, tracer);\r\n    //processor.Execute(transaction, header, tracer);\r\n    processor.Trace(transaction, header, tracer);\r\n    //processor.BuildUp(transaction, header, tracer);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is bug, or i do something wrong?\r\n",
